From: KOSHIKAWA Kenichi <reishoku.misc@pm.me>
Date: 2026-01-28
Subject: rpmdev-spectool: lazy import rpm module

help2man runs rpmdev-spectool just for usage text. Importing the rpm
module at top-level can fail in minimal environments, which breaks
manpage generation. Lazy-load rpm only when needed.

---
 rpmdev-spectool | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/rpmdev-spectool
+++ b/rpmdev-spectool
@@ -28,7 +28,6 @@ import tempfile
 import time
 from collections import OrderedDict
 from typing import Optional
 from urllib.parse import urlparse
 
 import progressbar
 import requests
-import rpm
@@ -143,6 +142,8 @@ class Spec:
     def __init__(self, path: str):
         self.path = path
-        self.spec = rpm.spec(self.path)
+        import rpm
+
+        self.spec = rpm.spec(self.path)
@@ -404,6 +405,8 @@ def main() -> int:
         if args["directory"]:
             directory = args["directory"]
         elif args["sourcedir"]:
+            import rpm
+
             directory = rpm.expandMacro("%{_sourcedir}")
         else:
             directory = os.getcwd()
